        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have been too dilatory in answering your kind letter. I am much obliged for your suggestions respecting the deficiencies in my indications of the localities of the species. I wish much to supply these &amp; other imperfections in my descriptions, but I cannot venture to publish on the Chalcidites at my own expence, &amp; the subject is too unpopular to be readily received into periodical works. As soon as I have leisure I will obtain the loan of your Specimens, &amp; answer your queries fully. Meanwhile I will just state that with a few exceptions the Chalcidites of S. America, &amp; also those of Australia are remarkably like the European species, many of them are very nearly allied to the British species, &amp; 2 or 3 are absolutely identical with the latter.</p>
<p>Believe me my Dear Sir | Yours very truly | Francis Walker <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> July 6.<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></p>
<p>Grove Cottage | Southgate</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
    
        
